VERSION 1
WHEN PRESENT \bstatic\s+\w+\s*\(
WHEN EXPR PRESENT:static\s+\w+.*=\s*\w+::|static\s+\w+.*getInstance\(\)|Singleton && MISSING:constexpr|constinit|test|example
REPORT AS area_of_interest
REASON Detects potential cycles during the initialization of static objects, which can lead to undefined behavior.
TRACE Externalized rule logic for Static Object Initialization Cycles: Undefined Behavior Risk.
